# Modelfile for Granite Switch (dense Granite-4.1 + 12 embedded LoRA adapters,
# selected per-token by control tokens).
#
# The GGUF carries everything Ollama needs:
#   - the custom `graniteswitch.*` metadata keys (num_adapters, adapter_token_ids,
#     adapter_substitute_token_ids, max_lora_rank),
#   - the stacked LoRA tensors (blk.N.attn_qkv.lora_a_q ... dim = 12 adapters + 1 base slot),
#   - the tokenizer (incl. the control tokens) and the embedded chat template.
#
# `ollama create` preserves all of that verbatim; the `graniteswitch` arch is
# validated at RUN time by the patched llama-server runner. So this Modelfile is
# intentionally minimal — no hand-authored TEMPLATE, we rely on the GGUF's
# embedded tokenizer.chat_template.
#
# Build the GGUF with this repo's llama.cpp fork converter, or reuse the verified
# gs-f16.gguf (842 tensors, stacked dim 13). Point FROM at wherever it lives.
#
# Usage:
#   ollama create granite-switch -f Modelfile.granite-switch
#   ollama run granite-switch
#
# For the mid-sequence adapter-switch demos, use the raw /api/generate endpoint
# (raw:true) so control tokens reach the model untemplated — see OLLAMA.md.

FROM ./gs-f16.gguf

# Greedy decode makes the adapter behaviour deterministic and easy to compare
# against the llama.cpp `llama-completion --temp 0` reference.
PARAMETER temperature 0
